activities.name: Visit number
activities.description: Visit number

activities.name: Days from randomization
activities.description: Days from randomization

activities.name: Visit interval tolerance (days)
activities.description: Visit interval tolerance (days)

activities.name: Prescreening informed consent
activities.description: Prescreening informed consent

activities.name: Informed consent
activities.description: The ICF must be signed before any protocol-specific tests or procedures are performed

activities.name: Inclusion and exclusion criteria, review and confirm
activities.description: Inclusion and exclusion criteria should be confirmed prior to drug assignment and administration of first dose of study intervention

activities.name: Ascertainment of high risk for cardiovascular events
activities.description: High risk for cardiovascular events will be defined as CAD, stroke, or peripheral artery disease, or ASCVD risk equivalents (familial hypercholesterolemia or type 2 diabetes)

activities.name: Demographics
activities.description: Includes year of birth, sex, ethnicity (where permissible), and race

activities.name: Preexisting conditions and medical history, including relevant surgical history
activities.description: All conditions ongoing and relevant past surgical and medical history should be collected

activities.name: Prespecified medical history (indication and history of interest)
activities.description: Prespecified medical history includes history of cardiovascular events

activities.name: Prior treatments for indication
activities.description: Relevant prior therapies include, but are not limited to, lipid-lowering medications

activities.name: Substance use (alcohol, caffeine, and tobacco use)
activities.description: Substance use (alcohol, caffeine, and tobacco use)

activities.name: Concomitant medications
activities.description: Additional data will be collected for medications of interest

activities.name: AEs
activities.description: Any events that occur after signing the informed consent are considered AEs as defined. Additional data are collected for certain AEs

activities.name: Height
activities.description: Participant should remove shoes

activities.name: Weight
activities.description: Participant should remove shoes

activities.name: Vital signs
activities.description: Includes pulse rate and blood pressure measured after participant has been sitting at least 5 minutes and before ECG tracing and collection of blood samples for laboratory testing

activities.name: Physical examination
activities.description: The physical examination is performed (excludes pelvic, rectal, and breast examinations unless clinically indicated)

activities.name: Symptom-directed physical assessment
activities.description: Symptom-directed physical assessment will be conducted at the discretion of the PI or qualified personnel, per local regulations, as indicated based on participant status and standard of care

activities.name: 12-Lead ECG (local)
activities.description: Collect single, local ECG prior to collection of blood samples for laboratory testing, including PK samples. Participants should be supine for approximately 5 to 10 minutes before ECG collections and remain supine but awake during the ECG collection

activities.name: Hematology
activities.description: Hematology

activities.name: Clinical chemistry
activities.description: Clinical chemistry

activities.name: Lipid panel
activities.description: Lipid panel

activities.name: Urinalysis
activities.description: Urinalysis

activities.name: UACR
activities.description: Urine albumin creatinine ratio

activities.name: Serum pregnancy
activities.description: Females only

activities.name: FSH
activities.description: Optional; performed as needed to confirm postmenopausal status

activities.name: TSH
activities.description: Thyroid stimulating hormone

activities.name: HbA1c
activities.description: Hemoglobin A1c

activities.name: Lp(a)
activities.description: Lipoprotein(a)

activities.name: ApoB
activities.description: Apolipoprotein B

activities.name: hsCRP
activities.description: High-sensitivity C-reactive protein

activities.name: HIV screening test
activities.description: HIV screening test

activities.name: HCV screening test
activities.description: If HCV antibody test is positive, it must be followed by an HCV RNA test

activities.name: HBV screening test
activities.description: If HBsAg is negative and HBcAb is positive, further testing with HBV DNA is required. If the screening HBV DNA is negative, the participant is not excluded

activities.name: eGFR
activities.description: Calculated using CKD-EPI method

activities.name: Postdose PK sample
activities.description: Visit 2: Collect 2 samples (0.5 hours postdose, 4-9 hours postdose). Visit 7: Collect 1 sample (24-36 hours postdose)

activities.name: Immunogenicity (ADA)
activities.description: Visit 2 and 7 will be collected predose

activities.name: PK sample for immunogenicity
activities.description: Collect a time-matched PK sample for all scheduled and unscheduled immunogenicity samples. Visit 7 will be collected predose

activities.name: Optional genetics sample
activities.description: Sample can be obtained at or after the specified visit

activities.name: Exploratory biomarker samples
activities.description: On dosing days, collect samples before dosing

activities.name: Register visit with IWRS
activities.description: Unscheduled visits are not required to be registered in IWRS

activities.description: Randomization via IWRS
